{{Incomplete|date=July 2013}}
[[File:Native woman of Dasamonquepeio (1590).jpg|thumb|320px||right|Full-length, front and back portraits of a native woman from [[Dasamonquepeio]] of the Americas showing manner of dress and way of carrying a child on her back; view of river and landscape in the background, (1590).]]
'''Women in the Americas''' are women who were born in, who live in, and are from the [[Americas]]. By regional division, these women are the women from [[Women in North America|North America]] and those that are from [[Women in South America|South America]]. Some of these women can also be designated as women in [[Central America]] or women in [[Middle America (region)|Middle America]]. Some women of the Americas come from the [[Carribean]] region. Their evolution, culture and history coincide with the [[History of the Americas|history]] of the [[American continent]] itself.

Some North American women come from [[dependencies and other territories]] such as those women from [[Women in Anguilla|Anguilla]] (United Kingdom), [[Women in Aruba|Aruba]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), [[Women in Bermuda|Bermuda]] (United Kingdom), [[Women in Bonaire|Bonaire]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), the [[Women in the British Virgin Islands|British Virgin Islands]] (United Kingdom), [[Women in the Cayman Islands|Cayman Islands]] (United Kingdom), [[Women in Cura<U+00E7>ao|Cura<U+00E7>ao]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), [[Women in Greenland|Greenland]] ([[Kingdom of Denmark]]), [[Women in Guadeloupe|Guadeloupe]] ([[France]]), [[Women in Martinique|Martinique]] (France), [[Women in Montserrat|Montserrat]] (United Kingdom), [[Women in Puerto Rico|Puerto Rico]] (United States), [[Women in Saint Barth<U+00E9>lemy|Saint Barth<U+00E9>lemy]] (France), [[Women in Saint Martin|Saint Martin]] (France), [[Women in Saint Pierre and Miquelon|Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] (France), [[Women in Saba|Saba]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), [[Women in Sint Eustatius|Sint Eustatius]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), [[Women in Sint Maarten|Sint Maarten]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), [[Women in Turks and Caicos Islands|Turks and Caicos Islands]] (United Kingdom), and the [[Women in the United States Virgin Islands|United States Virgin Islands]] ([[United States]]).

Some South American women come from dependencies and other territories like those that are from [[Women in Aruba|Aruba]] ([[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]), [[Women in Bonaire|Bonaire]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), [[Women in Cura<U+00E7>ao|Cura<U+00E7>ao]] (Kingdom of the Netherlands), the [[Women in the Falkland Islands|Falkland Islands]] ([[United Kingdom]]), [[Women in French Guiana|French Guiana]] ([[France]]), [[Women in South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands|South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands]] (United Kingdom).

==North America==
Women from [[North America]] include women residing in [[Women in Antigua and Bermuda|Antigua and Barbuda]], the [[Women in the Bahamas|Bahamas]], [[Women in Barbados|Barbados]], [[Women in Belize|Belize]], [[Women in Canada|Canada]], [[Women in Costa Rica|Costa Rica]], [[Women in Cuba|Cuba]], [[Women in Dominica|Dominica]], the [[Women in the Dominican Republic|Dominican Republic]], [[Women in El Salvador|El Salvador]], [[Women in Grenada|Grenada]], [[Women in Guatemala|Guatemala]], [[Women in Haiti|Haiti]], [[Women in Honduras|Honduras]], [[Women in Jamaica|Jamaica]], [[Women in Mexico|Mexico]], [[Women in Nicaragua|Nicaragua]], [[Women in Panama|Panama]], [[Women in Saint Kitts and Nevis|Saint Kitts and Nevis]], [[Women in Saint Lucia|Saint Lucia]], [[Women in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]], [[Women in Trinidad and Tobago|Trinidad and Tobago]], and the [[Women in the United States|United States]].
