===Cuba===
{{Main|Women in Cuba}}
'''Cuban women''' have equal [[constitution of Cuba|constitutional]] rights as men in the [[economy of Cuba|economic]], [[Politics of Cuba|political]], [[Culture of Cuba|cultural]] and social fields, as well as in the family. According to article 44 of the Cuban Constitution, the state guarantees women the same opportunities and possibilities as men, in order to achieve woman<U+2019>s full participation in the development of the country. Women hold 48.9% of the parliamentary seats in the [[Cuban National Assembly]] ranking sixth of 162 countries on issues of female participation in political life. [http://hdr.undp.org/statistics/data/country_fact_sheets/cty_fs_CUB.html] There has been only one candidate per seat and the National Candidacy Commission decides the persons.<ref>[http://www.granma.co.cu/secciones/candidatos/nuestros_diputados.htm Granma].</ref><ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/2079_B.htm IPU Parline].</ref><ref>[http://www.cubanet.org/CNews/y07/oct07/18e9.htm]</ref><ref>[http://www.cubanet.org/CNews/y98/jan98/26e1.htm]</ref>

