==Central America==
Women living in [[Central America]] (or [[Middle America (region)|Middle America]]; see also [[Mesoamerica]]) may include those that are from [[Women in Belize|Belize]], [[Women in Costa Rica|Costa Rica]], [[Women in El Salvador|El Salvador]], [[Women in Guatemala|Guatemala]], [[Women in Honduras|Honduras]], [[Women in Nicaragua|Nicaragua]], and [[Women in Panama|Panama]]. If the term "women in Middle America", this regional grouping may include [[women from Antigua and Barbuda]], the [[Women in the Bahamas|Bahamas]], [[Women in Barbados|Barbados]], [[Women in Belize|Belize]], [[Women in Costa Rica|Costa Rica]], [[Women in Cuba|Cuba]], [[Women in Dominica|Dominica]], [[Women in the Dominican Republic|Dominican Republic]], [[Women in El Salvador|El Salvador]], [[Women in Grenada|Grenada]], [[Women in Guatemala|Guatemala]], [[Women in Haiti|Haiti]], [[Women in Honduras|Honduras]], [[Women in Jamaica|Jamaica]], [[Women in Mexico|Mexico]], [[Women in Nicaragua|Nicaragua]], [[Women in Panama|Panama]], [[Women in Saint Kitts and Nevis|Saint Kitts and Nevis]], [[Women in Saint Lucia|Saint Lucia]], [[Women in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]], and [[Women in Trinidad and Tobago|Trinidad and Tobago]]. If the term "women in Mesoamerica" is used, the women may come approximately from central [[Mexico]] to [[Belize]], [[Guatemala]], [[El Salvador]], [[Honduras]], [[Nicaragua]], and northern [[Costa Rica]]. 

For this article, only those women that are categorically from "Central America" are presented in this section. 
